Added legend support to kdeplot()Added a legend keyword to kdeplot() so that users can toggle legendsnwhen displaying, e.g., multiple densities on the same plot. Labels donnot override the legend setting, so you need to assign labels and setnlegend to True in order to see the legend as expected.n

Added example of the legend keyword in kdeplot.I added an example demonstrating how to use the legend keyword withnkdeplot. I also checked all of the distplot examples to make sure thatnthere are no side effects. I also tested the example at cell 21 (Toncontrol any of the underlying plots, pass keyword arguments to then[plot]_kws argument.) using values of True and False for the displotnlegend keyword. No problems were observed, and I set it back to Falsento match the original notebook.n

Assign lable name for legends using DataFrame or Series nameCheck for a name attribute on the input and automatically set that asnthe label if it exists for Pandas DataFrames and Series. If the usernspecifies a label in the call to kdeplot it will take precedence overnthe name attribute. If no label is provided and there is no namenattribute then a default value of kde is assogned.n
Changed to duck typing for name detectionIf the input data has a name attribute, use it for a label if one isnnot slready set.n

More work on kdeplot and legendsDid more work on legend handling in kdeplot.nnMade changes to label and legend handling in distplot. added keywordnkde_label (defaults to False). If it's set to True, thennkde_kws[label] is set to kde, and the KDE in the resulting plotnwill be labeled kde.nnAdded more complete description of how to use kdeplot labels tonnotebook. Added  example of vertical kdeplots.n

Compute linkage correctly when fastcluster is not installed.When fastcluster is not installed, _calculate_linkage_scipy is used toncompute linkages. It contained an erroneous call to squareform().ndistance.pdist() already returns a condensed distance matrix that isnrequired as input for the linkage() function. Converting it to a matrixnwith squareform() is possible and linkage() will accept the resultingnmatrix, but consider it to be a matrix with vectors of observations and runndistance.pdist() again on it. Thus, we got a linkage based on distancesnbetween distances.n

Sort numerical category levels by defaultAdds an additional rule when determining category order in categorical plots.nNow, when numeric variables are used in a categorical role, the defaultnbehavior is to sort the unique levels of the variable (i.e they will be innproper numerical order). This can still be overriden by the appropriaten``{*_}order`` parameter, and variables with a ``category`` dtype will stillnfollow the category order even if the levels are strictly numerical.n

Fix #719 by converting the format templates in FacetGrid.set_titles() to Unicode.This commit adds the function ``to_utf8`` to utils.py which reliablynconverts Python objects to unicode strings both in Python 2.7 and 3.x. Thisnfunction is used in ``FacetGrid.set_titles()`` to ensure that the stringnformat templates used in the plot titles are always unicode strings.nnThe function ``to_utf8`` is somewhat similar in spirit to the one suggestednin #724. Getting the skip to work again is a bit more effort.nnThe other major change is around pandas module privacy. The `pandas.util.testing`nmodule is now private. Common methods like `assert_frame_equal` are now availablenin the public `pandas.testing` module. Seaaborn is also using a few now-privatenmethods from pandas.core. I'll followup with fixes for those later (shouldn't seenany deprecation warnings in the meantime).n
